# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-onboard

Model/effort: Haiku / low.

Brings a new human or agent into the operating model. A guided, read-only walkthrough
of how the system is run — the contract, the planes, the ritual, and the commands.

## Steps
1. Read and summarize the operating contract: the one rule, the two state planes, the
   branch model, and multi-agent claim-check-warn.
2. Explain the session ritual (open and close) and that the hooks run it automatically.
3. Point to the map of the system: the brain repo, the `app_repos` in the manifest, and
   the capabilities map for what exists.
4. List the `{{CMD_PREFIX}}-*` command set and when to reach for each, with the model/effort
   tiers.
5. Show how to claim work safely (check overlap, self-assign, branch early) and how to
   close it.
6. Confirm understanding; make no changes to brain or app state.

## Done when
The newcomer can state the two planes, run the ritual, and knows which command to use for
common tasks — with nothing written.
